The paper deals with a visual dialogue task and proposes a method for question generation based on visual dialogue state tracking. This involves the use of object representations and attention mechanisms to generate new questions. Given this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these fields are also relevant to the task of visual dialogue and question generation.
